New Records: Zack Wheeler earned his 100th career victory
Key Match Events: Edmundo Sosa homered, doubled and drove in two runs
Trea Turner also went deep for NL East-leading Philadelphia
Michael Harris II robbed Austin Hays of a home run with a stellar, highlight-reel catch
Pre-Game Insights: Phillies manager Rob Thomson said Zack Wheeler was 'locked in tonight'
Post-Match Reflections: Zack Wheeler said his 100th victory was'special' and 'a long road'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillies have won six of eight games
The Phillies lead the Braves in the division by six games
Zack Wheeler threw 65 of his 96 pitches for strikes
Michael Harris II's catch was called 'the catch of the year' by Atlanta manager Brian Snitker
Others: The Braves' Max Fried gave up three runs on five hits with four strikeouts and four walks in seven innings
